      "writtenOn": "2020-04-30T06:46:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Currently, if rdb_channel fails to upload test results due to non-transient errors, then the results are simply dropped.\n\nIIUC, sink should terminate the server immediately in a failure of result/artifact uploads, and s.Err() should return the error.\n\nIs this correct? then, I will add a TODO and make the change in a separate CL.\n\n\u003e\u003e I think we should either return nil in Shutdown and here if server was closed as expected, or create a new sentinel error variable in this package and return that.\nDone. PTAL",
